      "side": 1,
      "message": "this means the number of reads for each CounterShard is number of rows we insert? this defeats the purpose of the sharded counter. One transaction should touch exactly one shard row, increment it by the number of results we are inserting, and write that. The generality hurts performance.\n\n\n---\n\nstepping back, i just realized that, if we are going to have one bot writing to one invocation at a time, i.e. we have one writer at a time anyway, then we don\u0027t actually benefit from sharded counters. So i now think we don\u0027t need to shard the counter. We could keep the count in the invocation actually. WDYT?",
      "revId": "f7901f5816ba144b2eb15c4c7a6cfbb48d1eb6d1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
